the weights are the weights used for the first block of the ring ordering.
@item @strong{Note:}
@code{ord(0)} is @code{-1}.
@*In a global degree ordering @code{ord} is the same as @code{deg}.
@item @strong{Example:}
@smallexample
@c example
  ring r=7,(x,y),wp(2,3);
  ord(0);
  poly f=x2+y3;  // weight on y is 3
  ord(f),deg(f);
  ring R=7,(x,y),ws(2,3);
  poly f=x2+y3;
  ord(f),deg(f);
  vector v=[x2,y];
  ord(v),deg(v);
@c example
@end smallexample
